The official documentation can be found here: https://www.opensense.network/progprak/beta/apidocs/#/ This file will become your README and also the index of your documentation.

Install¶

Put this whole folder in your project, and then do import osnapi as api.
pip install your_project_name

How to use¶

if you want to use functions that require a login, use api.login(username, password). After successfully logging in, the username and password you used, as well as the token that was returned by the server, are stored inside the Settings object.
The default api_enpoint is "https://dep2.osn.k8s.ise-apps.de/api/v1.0". It is also stored inside the Settings object.
Except for the api_endpoint, the other three Settings are not defined when you import the package.
